# Development Setup

1. ensure you have go installed
2. ensure you have a .env file in the root of the project with the following variables as shown in .env.example
3. docker daemon is running
4. To spin up the local databases, from the root of the project run the following command

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

5. To apply the migrations, from the root of the project run the following command

```bash
make migrate-up
```

6. To install the dependencies, from the root of the project run the following command

```bash
go mod tidy
```

7. To run the dev server, ensure you have air installed. You can get it from [here](https://github.com/cosmtrek/air). Then run the following command from root of the project

```bash
air
```
